WEBVTT

00:00:10.260 --> 00:00:13.388
[NARRATOR] As Jirukoma departed
with his group of volunteers,

00:00:13.430 --> 00:00:15.224
leaving Friedonia behind them,

00:00:15.265 --> 00:00:19.061
his sister Komain took over
as chief of the settlement.

00:00:19.102 --> 00:00:21.063
Those traveling could
not shake their longing

00:00:21.104 --> 00:00:23.315
for home and swore
to take back their lands,

00:00:23.357 --> 00:00:25.484
by force, if necessary.

00:00:25.526 --> 00:00:27.361
While those who saw them
off kept their longing

00:00:27.402 --> 00:00:30.572
for home in their hearts,
dreaming of restoring peace

00:00:30.614 --> 00:00:34.743
to their nations while
remaining in a foreign land.

00:00:34.785 --> 00:00:37.037
Though their parting
was a sad one,

00:00:37.079 --> 00:00:40.332
at the same time,
it was their own decision.

00:02:18.722 --> 00:02:21.558
I see you made it
to class on time.

00:02:21.600 --> 00:02:24.227
Oh. Yes, I'm wearing glasses.

00:02:24.269 --> 00:02:25.896
Not that I need them.

00:02:25.937 --> 00:02:27.773
They put me in the teacher mood.

00:02:27.814 --> 00:02:29.483
[AISHA]
Like a piece of armor?

00:02:29.524 --> 00:02:30.484
Indeed.

00:02:30.525 --> 00:02:33.904
For you see, this will be
your first of many lessons.

00:02:33.945 --> 00:02:37.991
So welcome to day one of
the Fiancée's Bridal Course.

00:02:39.910 --> 00:02:42.329
And your teacher will be
none other than myself,

00:02:42.371 --> 00:02:44.665
the learned Excel Walter.

00:02:47.292 --> 00:02:49.836
To be candid, I've been
hoping for an opportunity

00:02:49.878 --> 00:02:51.338
like this for quite a while,

00:02:51.380 --> 00:02:53.090
and when I heard His Majesty
say that he could

00:02:53.131 --> 00:02:54.925
have children any time now,

00:02:54.966 --> 00:02:57.386
I decided this would
be the perfect moment.

00:02:57.427 --> 00:02:59.846
After all, it won't be
long before all of you

00:02:59.888 --> 00:03:01.348
will be mothers.

00:03:01.390 --> 00:03:04.893
As you are aware,
this Kingdom faced civil war.

00:03:04.935 --> 00:03:06.978
Two generations ago
when the king died,

00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:09.022
a dispute arose over
who would succeed

00:03:09.064 --> 00:03:10.273
to the throne.

00:03:10.315 --> 00:03:13.068
The royal family
was nearly wiped out.

00:03:13.110 --> 00:03:15.278
Under His Majesty Souma's rule,

00:03:15.320 --> 00:03:17.739
I trust nothing of the
sort will happen again.

00:03:17.781 --> 00:03:18.573
However!

00:03:18.615 --> 00:03:20.450
You mustn't be complacent!

00:03:20.492 --> 00:03:22.619
If there is any breach
between king and queen

00:03:22.661 --> 00:03:24.955
or between a queen and
one of the other queens,

00:03:24.996 --> 00:03:27.916
someone will certainly
try taking advantage of it!

00:03:28.959 --> 00:03:30.293
For the sake of the kingdom,

00:03:30.335 --> 00:03:32.838
it is paramount for all
of you to establish

00:03:32.879 --> 00:03:37.008
a harmonious
marital relationship!

00:03:37.050 --> 00:03:40.971
Thus, why a bridal training
course is so crucial!

00:03:41.012 --> 00:03:43.807
Uh, but why are you
the one teaching us,

00:03:43.849 --> 00:03:46.476
Duchess Walter?

00:03:46.518 --> 00:03:50.021
Well, I have lived for
over 500 years now.

00:03:50.063 --> 00:03:53.066
And fallen in love with
a number of gentlemen,

00:03:53.108 --> 00:03:55.736
none of whom I ever
parted with, mind you,

00:03:55.777 --> 00:03:57.362
except through death.

00:03:57.404 --> 00:04:01.116
Not to mention I have also
borne each of them children.

00:04:01.158 --> 00:04:04.286
Now it's my responsibility
to teach you as queens--

00:04:04.327 --> 00:04:06.955
no, rather as individual women,

00:04:06.997 --> 00:04:10.167
how to remain in harmony
with the man that you love.

00:04:10.208 --> 00:04:11.543
The art of being a wife,

00:04:11.585 --> 00:04:13.795
everything from
understanding the male mind

00:04:13.837 --> 00:04:17.466
to ensuring a smooth married
life via the performance of,

00:04:17.507 --> 00:04:20.010
shall we say,
nighttime "services."

00:04:21.970 --> 00:04:24.097
I've already had
His Majesty Souma

00:04:24.139 --> 00:04:25.974
take an individual
course with me.

00:04:27.768 --> 00:04:31.271
Now then, what does this mean
in both war and marriage?

00:04:31.313 --> 00:04:34.107
Information is key if
you want to succeed.

00:04:34.149 --> 00:04:35.859
"Know yourself and the enemy,

00:04:35.901 --> 00:04:37.903
and you'll survive
a hundred battles".

00:04:37.944 --> 00:04:40.614
As His Majesty is
always fond of saying.

00:04:40.655 --> 00:04:41.907
He's right.

00:04:41.948 --> 00:04:44.409
As long as you are aware
of how the other party

00:04:44.451 --> 00:04:48.246
views you, you will always
know how to conduct yourself.

00:04:48.288 --> 00:04:51.333
Still though, sometimes it
is good to be unpredictable

00:04:51.374 --> 00:04:54.503
and shake things up if you
ever find yourself in a rut.

00:04:54.544 --> 00:04:56.671
Know yourself, brides,
and the other party,

00:04:56.713 --> 00:04:59.049
and your union
won't be endangered.

00:05:01.927 --> 00:05:03.053
Like I said.

00:05:03.094 --> 00:05:06.306
I met with the king,
along with a royal mage,

00:05:06.348 --> 00:05:10.018
who secretly cast a confession
spell on His Majesty.

00:05:10.060 --> 00:05:12.687
This notebook contains
the information I got

00:05:12.729 --> 00:05:15.023
out of him during that session.

00:05:21.613 --> 00:05:22.447
All right.

00:05:22.489 --> 00:05:25.158
I will now read how
His Majesty Souma

00:05:25.200 --> 00:05:28.119
sees each of his future
queens, one-by-one.

00:05:29.621 --> 00:05:31.581
First, Roroa.

00:05:31.623 --> 00:05:34.209
I'll start with his
estimation of you.

00:05:34.251 --> 00:05:36.378
Me?! Why do I go first?

00:05:36.419 --> 00:05:38.547
Oh, no particular reason.

00:05:38.588 --> 00:05:40.298
I just thought I'd start
with the latest one

00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:42.509
to meet His Majesty.

00:05:42.551 --> 00:05:43.885
Yeah, that makes sense,

00:05:43.927 --> 00:05:46.763
since I am the newest
addition to this group.

00:05:46.805 --> 00:05:50.559
Plus, I suppose it's
better than going last.

00:05:50.600 --> 00:05:52.811
[EXCEL] All right, so
according to His Majesty...

00:05:54.354 --> 00:05:55.814
[EXCEL] Why don't we
talk about Roroa

00:05:55.856 --> 00:05:58.024
and your feelings for her.

00:05:58.066 --> 00:05:59.401
My feelings?

00:05:59.442 --> 00:06:02.737
I like how cheerful
and friendly she can be.

00:06:02.779 --> 00:06:04.948
She can be underhanded at times,

00:06:04.990 --> 00:06:07.784
but that's just part
of her charm.

00:06:07.826 --> 00:06:09.828
It's heartwarming how
she looks up to Liscia

00:06:09.870 --> 00:06:11.121
and the others.

00:06:11.162 --> 00:06:15.000
Also, she's a wiz when
it comes to finances.

00:06:15.041 --> 00:06:18.211
I'm very grateful for her
and that she's my fiancée.

00:06:21.631 --> 00:06:24.843
Th-This is so embarrassing.

00:06:24.885 --> 00:06:26.219
And furthermore,

00:06:26.261 --> 00:06:28.847
I asked His Majesty if
he had anything to add

00:06:28.889 --> 00:06:30.765
and he said the following:

00:06:30.807 --> 00:06:32.851
"Regarding the death
of her father,

00:06:32.893 --> 00:06:34.686
I feel responsible for it."

00:06:37.105 --> 00:06:39.190
[SOUMA]
I know we were at war.

00:06:39.232 --> 00:06:40.901
But that hardly matters.

00:06:40.942 --> 00:06:43.361
His blood is on my hands.

00:06:43.403 --> 00:06:45.655
And while I know Roroa
says she was estranged

00:06:45.697 --> 00:06:47.198
from Gaius,

00:06:47.240 --> 00:06:50.243
I wonder, does she
really want to marry me?

00:06:51.161 --> 00:06:52.871
That worries him sometimes.

00:06:55.832 --> 00:06:57.751
What? Is he dense?

00:06:57.792 --> 00:06:59.419
Darling, you big dummy!

00:06:59.461 --> 00:07:01.546
I've already
considered all of that!

00:07:01.588 --> 00:07:03.381
I'm getting married to
him because that's what

00:07:03.423 --> 00:07:05.717
I really wanted to do,
so why's he thinkin'

00:07:05.759 --> 00:07:06.968
about the past?

00:07:08.011 --> 00:07:09.846
[crying]

00:07:11.556 --> 00:07:12.724
[crying]

00:07:12.766 --> 00:07:14.267
There, there.

00:07:14.309 --> 00:07:16.895
[ROROA]
Big sister Cia.

00:07:16.937 --> 00:07:18.605
Don't you worry.

00:07:18.647 --> 00:07:21.191
I'll give Souma a piece
of my mind later.

00:07:22.275 --> 00:07:25.403
Roroa, there's a reason
he brought it up, you know.

00:07:25.445 --> 00:07:27.113
That's because he loves you.

00:07:27.155 --> 00:07:28.949
You're important to him.

00:07:28.990 --> 00:07:30.951
You know that, don't you?

00:07:30.992 --> 00:07:33.453
[ROROA]
Mm-hmm.

00:07:33.495 --> 00:07:35.747
While on the one hand,
I'm upset he's oblivious

00:07:35.789 --> 00:07:37.082
to the way I feel--

00:07:37.123 --> 00:07:39.209
on the other, now that
I know just how highly

00:07:39.250 --> 00:07:43.046
my darling thinks of me,
it makes me kinda happy.

00:07:43.088 --> 00:07:44.756
[EXCEL]
As long as you're aware of that,

00:07:44.798 --> 00:07:46.633
you should do just fine.

00:07:46.675 --> 00:07:48.343
Next up, Juna.

00:07:48.385 --> 00:07:49.302
Yes?

00:07:52.097 --> 00:07:54.766
Pretty. Beautiful.

00:07:54.808 --> 00:07:56.851
Her appearance.

00:07:56.893 --> 00:07:58.728
But it's not only that.

00:07:58.770 --> 00:08:00.897
Her heart, too.

00:08:00.939 --> 00:08:03.650
She walks behind the rest,
but only because

00:08:03.692 --> 00:08:06.653
she wants to see
the larger picture.

00:08:06.695 --> 00:08:09.614
She really is the perfect woman.

00:08:09.656 --> 00:08:12.033
I don't want to lose her.

00:08:12.075 --> 00:08:15.787
His Majesty really
said that about me?

00:08:15.829 --> 00:08:18.289
When I asked, "How do
you feel about Juna?"

00:08:18.331 --> 00:08:20.667
he then replied
with the following:

00:08:20.709 --> 00:08:23.044
"I consider myself lucky
whenever she lets me

00:08:23.086 --> 00:08:26.548
dote on her, especially
since I'm a younger guy."

00:08:26.589 --> 00:08:27.507
[JUNA]
Wait a minute.

00:08:27.549 --> 00:08:30.135
I thought His Majesty and
myself were the same age.

00:08:30.176 --> 00:08:31.261
[LISCIA]
No, she's right.

00:08:31.302 --> 00:08:32.595
They're both 19.

00:08:35.306 --> 00:08:37.809
It was only later
Souma realized,

00:08:37.851 --> 00:08:43.565
in the world where he came from,
that one year lasts 365 days.

00:08:43.606 --> 00:08:46.818
While in this one, it lasts 384,

00:08:46.860 --> 00:08:48.611
so when you factor
in the difference,

00:08:48.653 --> 00:08:51.573
you would actually be
at least a full year older

00:08:51.614 --> 00:08:53.450
than His Majesty Souma.

00:08:53.491 --> 00:08:55.326
I had no idea there
was such a gap between

00:08:55.368 --> 00:08:57.495
our ages. But wait!

00:08:57.537 --> 00:08:59.164
You're not saying that
His Majesty dislikes

00:08:59.205 --> 00:09:02.125
older women, are you?

00:09:02.167 --> 00:09:03.376
Not to worry.

00:09:03.418 --> 00:09:05.795
He continued by
saying the following:

00:09:05.837 --> 00:09:08.465
"In the world I come from
we have an old saying

00:09:08.506 --> 00:09:11.718
that goes, 'Find a wife a
year older than you are.

00:09:11.760 --> 00:09:15.055
And if necessary,
wear wire sandals."

00:09:15.096 --> 00:09:16.556
[JUNA]
Oh, thank goodness.

00:09:18.016 --> 00:09:19.309
[EXCEL]
Next up, Aisha.

00:09:19.350 --> 00:09:21.311
Y-Yes ma'am?

00:09:21.352 --> 00:09:25.273
[EXCEL] His Majesty Souma's
appraisal of you, Aisha, is...

00:09:27.192 --> 00:09:30.737
[AISHA] Um, sorry, but why
are you stopping there?

00:09:30.779 --> 00:09:31.654
[EXCEL]
Actually,

00:09:31.696 --> 00:09:32.822
he called you "pet-like."

00:09:32.864 --> 00:09:34.157
He said I'm what?!

00:09:35.950 --> 00:09:36.868
[DOG barks]

00:09:38.745 --> 00:09:39.871
I can see that.

00:09:39.913 --> 00:09:41.539
Not you, too, Juna!

00:09:41.581 --> 00:09:43.208
What am I, his lap dog?

00:09:44.542 --> 00:09:48.838
Aisha is strong and noble,
a gorgeous warrior.

00:09:48.880 --> 00:09:51.382
The fact is, she's the
most valiant fighter

00:09:51.424 --> 00:09:53.927
in the kingdom and it's
reassuring to know

00:09:53.968 --> 00:09:56.930
I always have her by my side.

00:09:56.971 --> 00:09:58.389
At least it should be.

00:10:00.058 --> 00:10:03.269
The thing is, there's something
irresistible about her.

00:10:03.311 --> 00:10:06.397
I find myself wanting
to protect her, I suppose.

00:10:09.109 --> 00:10:11.236
[AISHA] I'm an utter failure
as a bodyguard!

00:10:11.277 --> 00:10:13.321
[ROROA]
Aisha, shake.

00:10:13.363 --> 00:10:14.364
[AISHA]
Woof.

00:10:15.073 --> 00:10:16.991
You're so adorable.

00:10:17.033 --> 00:10:20.370
I feel like I want to
protect you, myself.

00:10:20.411 --> 00:10:22.122
What? Not you, too.

00:10:24.749 --> 00:10:28.419
[EXCEL] Lastly, we come
to Princess Liscia.

00:10:28.461 --> 00:10:30.547
I should start off by
mentioning I asked the king

00:10:30.588 --> 00:10:34.259
what was on his mind
when it comes to you.

00:10:34.300 --> 00:10:37.595
Uh, that feels like a different
question from the rest.

00:10:37.637 --> 00:10:38.847
[chuckles]

00:10:38.888 --> 00:10:41.182
I believe his assessment
of you Princess Liscia

00:10:41.224 --> 00:10:44.310
can be summarized by the
answer to that one inquiry.

00:10:44.352 --> 00:10:45.895
When his Majesty answered,

00:10:45.937 --> 00:10:48.898
he said just a single
word: "Nothing."

00:10:50.692 --> 00:10:52.569
[LISCIA]
"Nothing"? At all?

00:10:54.487 --> 00:10:56.281
He had something to say
about all the others,

00:10:56.322 --> 00:10:57.615
didn't he?

00:10:57.657 --> 00:11:01.536
And yet, when it came
to me, he drew a blank?

00:11:01.578 --> 00:11:04.664
