[ALL yell]

00:14:05.136 --> 00:14:07.472
[knocking]

00:14:07.513 --> 00:14:09.015
[MARIA]
Come on in.

00:14:09.057 --> 00:14:10.099
[JEANNE]
Pardon.

00:14:16.606 --> 00:14:19.400
I'm here to make my report
concerning the slave traders.

00:14:29.160 --> 00:14:31.662
So, the traders,
you have some news?

00:14:31.704 --> 00:14:33.039
I do.

00:14:33.081 --> 00:14:35.124
Similarly to Friedonia,

00:14:35.166 --> 00:14:37.543
I would like to start a
system where they instead

00:14:37.585 --> 00:14:39.253
work for the empire.

00:14:39.295 --> 00:14:41.381
That's Souma for
you, no surprise.

00:14:41.422 --> 00:14:43.341
Avoid a war by turning
all the slave traders

00:14:43.383 --> 00:14:44.759
into public servants.

00:14:44.801 --> 00:14:48.596
Meanwhile the slaves receive
a high-quality education.

00:14:48.638 --> 00:14:50.765
That couldn't have
been easy to think up.

00:14:50.807 --> 00:14:52.183
It wasn't Souma.

00:14:52.225 --> 00:14:53.851
I heard a slave trader
in town came up

00:14:53.893 --> 00:14:55.478
with the idea.

00:14:55.520 --> 00:14:56.854
My!

00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:58.731
Seems like they are
blessed with an abundance

00:14:58.773 --> 00:14:59.857
of talent.

00:14:59.899 --> 00:15:01.692
Indeed, they are.

00:15:01.734 --> 00:15:05.988
However, some slave traders
may not be sanctioned,

00:15:06.030 --> 00:15:09.492
and then commit violent
acts like kidnapping.

00:15:09.534 --> 00:15:11.828
It has happened in Friedonia.

00:15:11.869 --> 00:15:14.205
We will have to keep
a careful watch for that.

00:15:14.247 --> 00:15:15.289
Right.

00:15:15.331 --> 00:15:16.707
I would like to bear
that in mind when

00:15:16.749 --> 00:15:19.460
distributing certifications.

00:15:19.502 --> 00:15:20.920
You have to wonder,

00:15:20.962 --> 00:15:22.797
what kind of national
improvement is Souma

00:15:22.839 --> 00:15:24.882
going to try and implement next?

00:15:24.924 --> 00:15:27.301
If I know him, he's
imagining an even more

00:15:27.343 --> 00:15:29.470
wonderful kingdom.

00:15:29.512 --> 00:15:33.307
You certainly are taken
with His Majesty, sister.

00:15:33.349 --> 00:15:34.809
Of course I am!

00:15:34.851 --> 00:15:37.395
And yet, what Friedonia
attempts is ultimately

00:15:37.437 --> 00:15:39.021
just for reference.

00:15:39.063 --> 00:15:40.982
We have to do our
own building using

00:15:41.023 --> 00:15:43.526
the rock-solid foundation
of our country.

00:15:46.988 --> 00:15:48.948
A suggestion, if I may.

00:15:48.990 --> 00:15:50.616
As their progress continues,

00:15:50.658 --> 00:15:53.077
I should stay in
touch with Hakuya.

00:15:53.119 --> 00:15:56.205
Yes. I think that's best.

00:15:56.247 --> 00:15:59.000
So, how're things?

00:15:59.041 --> 00:16:00.543
With Hakuya, I mean.

00:16:02.420 --> 00:16:04.589
Th-There's nothing
going on between us!

00:16:04.630 --> 00:16:06.466
[HAKUYA sneezes]

00:16:06.507 --> 00:16:07.842
Pardon me, Your Majesty.

00:16:07.884 --> 00:16:10.344
That's okay. Please continue.

00:16:10.386 --> 00:16:12.722
[HAKUYA] The citizens' lives
have become more stable,

00:16:12.763 --> 00:16:15.725
which in turn has allowed us
to build more residences.

00:16:15.766 --> 00:16:17.059
That's terrific.

00:16:17.101 --> 00:16:20.354
[HAKUYA]
Alas, there is a problem.

00:16:20.396 --> 00:16:22.231
The trees surrounding
the capital have all been

00:16:22.273 --> 00:16:23.900
cut down for the
purpose of lumber

00:16:23.941 --> 00:16:25.735
and providing heat
for the winter.

00:16:25.776 --> 00:16:27.403
Some areas are
nothing but sparse,

00:16:27.445 --> 00:16:28.905
barren hills now.

00:16:28.946 --> 00:16:31.157
Seems we need lumber stoppages.

00:16:31.199 --> 00:16:33.159
Who would have guessed.

00:16:33.201 --> 00:16:34.952
[HAKUYA]
Lumber stoppages?

00:16:34.994 --> 00:16:37.747
Back where I'm from,
lumber was once an important

00:16:37.788 --> 00:16:39.582
military resource.

00:16:39.624 --> 00:16:41.792
To guard it, excess
logging was prohibited

00:16:41.834 --> 00:16:43.711
on certain mountains.

00:16:43.753 --> 00:16:46.005
It was so strict, they said
that felling a single tree

00:16:46.047 --> 00:16:47.340
could cost you your head.

00:16:47.381 --> 00:16:49.342
That seems a bit excessive.

00:16:49.383 --> 00:16:51.385
[SOUMA]
Well, we won't go that far.

00:16:51.427 --> 00:16:53.554
Also, redirect the
thinned timber from

00:16:53.596 --> 00:16:56.724
the God-Protected Forest
to where it's needed.

00:16:56.766 --> 00:16:58.142
As you wish, sire.

00:17:00.561 --> 00:17:01.979
The refugees.

00:17:02.021 --> 00:17:03.648
How're they and Komain?

00:17:03.689 --> 00:17:06.484
Their relocation is
going quite smoothly.

00:17:06.526 --> 00:17:09.070
And there are no
complaints with the housing.

00:17:09.111 --> 00:17:11.614
The issue is with jobs.

00:17:11.656 --> 00:17:14.492
While there are numerous
hunters among their people,

00:17:14.534 --> 00:17:16.327
the truth is, not many
of them possess

00:17:16.369 --> 00:17:19.288
what you would call
"marketable skills."

00:17:19.330 --> 00:17:21.916
We can't have them making
nothing but weapons.

00:17:21.958 --> 00:17:23.668
I see your point.

00:17:23.709 --> 00:17:25.670
They may hunt prey,
but they can also make

00:17:25.711 --> 00:17:26.963
woolen goods.

00:17:27.004 --> 00:17:29.966
Let's put them to work
in the textile mill.

00:17:30.007 --> 00:17:32.635
We have to invest
in the public sector more,

00:17:32.677 --> 00:17:35.596
and not just find
ways of employing them.

00:17:35.638 --> 00:17:38.099
[HAKUYA] Luckily, there are
some areas in Venetinova

00:17:38.140 --> 00:17:40.393
that as of yet have
not been zoned.

00:17:40.434 --> 00:17:42.395
We can develop the
facilities while providing

00:17:42.436 --> 00:17:44.397
jobs for the refugees.

00:17:44.438 --> 00:17:45.856
[SOUMA]
Go right ahead.

00:17:45.898 --> 00:17:47.900
As long as we continue
on this course,

00:17:47.942 --> 00:17:50.361
Venetinova will become
a center of trade.

00:17:50.403 --> 00:17:52.822
But unless we raise the
level of education there,

00:17:52.863 --> 00:17:54.615
they won't be able
to make ends meet.

00:17:54.657 --> 00:17:56.492
At least not on industry alone.

00:17:56.534 --> 00:17:59.036
I've thought as much and
have already discussed it

00:17:59.078 --> 00:18:00.288
with Ginger.

00:18:00.329 --> 00:18:02.039
Leave it to you, Hakuya.

00:18:02.081 --> 00:18:03.332
Zero moss.

00:18:03.374 --> 00:18:05.001
--[door opens]
--[PONCHO gasps]

00:18:08.170 --> 00:18:10.715
It's done!

00:18:10.756 --> 00:18:12.133
What's done, Poncho?

00:18:12.174 --> 00:18:15.386
[PONCHO] Th-The thing Your
Majesty specially requested

00:18:15.428 --> 00:18:16.637
I invent!

00:18:16.679 --> 00:18:18.681
Really? Are you
talking about "it"?

00:18:18.723 --> 00:18:19.890
[PONCHO]
Yes!

00:18:22.143 --> 00:18:23.102
May I try?

00:18:23.144 --> 00:18:25.646
I'd be honored if you
had a taste, sir, yes!

00:18:37.325 --> 00:18:38.784
Is it decent?

00:18:42.121 --> 00:18:43.748
You're a genius, Poncho!

00:18:43.789 --> 00:18:46.626
There's no doubt this is a
sauce for flour-based dishes!

00:18:46.667 --> 00:18:48.711
[PONCHO]
Yes!

00:18:48.753 --> 00:18:52.256
If I may ask, what makes this
sauce particularly important?

00:18:52.298 --> 00:18:53.924
Well, with this as a base,

00:18:53.966 --> 00:18:55.968
we can make
yakisoba, okonomiyaki,

00:18:56.010 --> 00:18:58.137
monjayaki, takoyaki!

00:18:58.179 --> 00:19:01.390
It'll even work as a sauce
poured over fried foods!

00:19:01.432 --> 00:19:02.850
How about a taste, Hakuya?

00:19:19.742 --> 00:19:22.286
[HAKUYA] It has a fruity,
veggie flavor with spices

00:19:22.328 --> 00:19:23.621
that entice the nose.

00:19:23.663 --> 00:19:26.207
And yet it's unlike ordinary
Worcestershire sauce

00:19:26.248 --> 00:19:29.043
in that it possesses a strong
sweet and sour flavor

00:19:29.085 --> 00:19:30.795
with no shortage of taste.

00:19:30.836 --> 00:19:34.090
Truly, it is unlike any
sauce I've had before!

00:19:34.131 --> 00:19:36.926
I admit, even I'm
surprised you reproduced it,

00:19:36.967 --> 00:19:39.345
considering how you've
never even tried it.

00:19:39.387 --> 00:19:42.640
Thank you for your generous
heaps of praise, yes!

00:19:42.682 --> 00:19:45.601
Still, just what did you use?

00:19:45.643 --> 00:19:47.770
Certain tastes
are familiar to me.

00:19:47.812 --> 00:19:50.064
[PONCHO] I'm impressed by
your palate, Your Majesty.

00:19:50.106 --> 00:19:52.066
Allow me to explain.

00:19:52.108 --> 00:19:54.276
It's a mixture of
various ingredients.

00:19:54.318 --> 00:19:57.113
First I combined Worcestershire
and tomato sauce,

00:19:57.154 --> 00:19:59.615
then added a little bit
of soy sauce and mirin

00:19:59.657 --> 00:20:02.743
from Kikkoro Distillery, yes.

00:20:02.785 --> 00:20:03.953
A question.

00:20:03.994 --> 00:20:06.288
Are we able to mass-produce
this new sauce?

00:20:06.330 --> 00:20:07.915
I spoke with Kikkoro Distillery,

00:20:07.957 --> 00:20:10.084
and they're willing
to take it on, yes.

00:20:10.126 --> 00:20:11.127
[HAKUYA]
Your Majesty.

00:20:11.168 --> 00:20:12.420
I just had a thought.

00:20:12.461 --> 00:20:14.588
What if we took food
that uses this flour-based

00:20:14.630 --> 00:20:16.882
dish sauce and made
it a specialty dish

00:20:16.924 --> 00:20:18.801
that you can only
get in Venetinova?

00:20:20.302 --> 00:20:22.555
Which in turn would
create new jobs!

00:20:22.596 --> 00:20:24.932
But we cannot let
Venetinova have a monopoly

00:20:24.974 --> 00:20:26.183
over this sauce!

00:20:26.225 --> 00:20:27.601
However, since
they're a gulf city,

00:20:27.643 --> 00:20:29.311
they can make squid yakisoba!

00:20:29.353 --> 00:20:31.564
This is the dawn of
a Venetinova delicacy!

00:20:31.605 --> 00:20:32.815
People will come from all over!

00:20:32.857 --> 00:20:34.358
Squid yakisoba?

00:20:34.400 --> 00:20:37.194
I have to be the first
in line to try some!

00:20:37.236 --> 00:20:40.448
My mouth's watering just
from imagining it, yes!

00:20:44.744 --> 00:20:47.538
[SOUMA] This sure has
been a turbulent year.

00:20:47.580 --> 00:20:49.331
Yes, you said it.

00:20:49.373 --> 00:20:50.833
[SOUMA] I had the throne
relinquished to me on

00:20:50.875 --> 00:20:55.296
April 32nd, and before you know
it, another year has passed.

00:20:55.337 --> 00:20:58.132
[LISCIA]
And tomorrow is December 32nd.

00:20:58.174 --> 00:20:59.967
The last eight months
felt like they went by

00:21:00.009 --> 00:21:01.260
in the blink of an eye.

00:21:10.352 --> 00:21:12.021
Liscia, is something wrong?

00:21:12.062 --> 00:21:13.564
Wrong?! What could be wrong?

00:21:13.606 --> 00:21:14.899
Nothing! That's what!

00:21:16.233 --> 00:21:18.694
Open. Say "ahh."

00:21:22.490 --> 00:21:25.451
I've always wanted more
moments just like this.

00:21:25.493 --> 00:21:27.870
You know, beneath the kotatsu,

00:21:27.912 --> 00:21:30.289
keeping warm,
while doing nothing.

00:21:30.331 --> 00:21:31.665
Sounds terrific, huh?

00:21:34.960 --> 00:21:37.338
[LISCIA]
Here. Say "ahh."

00:21:41.467 --> 00:21:43.552
It's nice taking
a break for once.

00:21:43.594 --> 00:21:46.555
True. Hopefully it stays
like this for a long while.

00:21:48.265 --> 00:21:49.517
Yeah, you said it.

00:21:51.560 --> 00:21:53.854
[knocking]

00:21:53.896 --> 00:21:57.191
[SOUMA] Then, as soon as we
say it's nice doing nothing...

00:21:57.233 --> 00:21:58.526
Yes?

00:21:58.567 --> 00:21:59.568
[door opens]

00:22:02.988 --> 00:22:05.366
[CARLA]
I have a message from Albert.

00:22:05.407 --> 00:22:08.452
Tomorrow, the evening
of December 32nd,

00:22:08.494 --> 00:22:10.955
he would like to meet
with Your Majesty.

00:22:10.996 --> 00:22:12.665
Finally.

00:22:12.706 --> 00:22:14.667
Wait, my father?

00:22:14.708 --> 00:22:16.877
Souma, I'm coming, too.

00:22:16.919 --> 00:22:18.838
His Majesty is to attend alone.

00:22:18.879 --> 00:22:20.214
Albert was specific.

